headline: Stronger Earnings, Higher Dividend and Capital Markets Push Could Be A Game Changer For Goldman Sachs Group (GS)
summary: In January 2026, The Goldman Sachs Group reported higher fourth-quarter 2025 net income of US$4,617 million and increased its quarterly dividend to US$4.50 per share, while also being active in issuing a range of fixed and floating rate senior and subordinated notes across multiple maturities. Together with continued expansion in asset and wealth management and a supportive backdrop for dealmaking and IPOs, these results highlight how Goldman Sachs is leaning on fee-based and capital markets...

headline: Goldman's Solomon on the State of Global Markets
summary: Goldman Sachs CEO David Solomon outlines key tailwinds and risks for the US economy and what they could mean for monetary policy in an exclusive interview with Bloomberg's Stephen Engle at the Goldman Sachs Global Macro Conference Asia-Pacific 2026.
